<article>
    <h1>SIN&#xAD;GA&#xAD;PORE CHI&#xAD;NESE FILM FES&#xAD;TI&#xAD;VAL 2020</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201009/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-10-09"><time>2020-10-09</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>In the Hong Kong drama Suk Suk (R21, 92 minutes, ), two older men are seen hav­ing drinks in a cafe, shop­ping at the wet mar­ket and sit­ting on a park bench.</p>
    <p>The “un­cles” – the film’s ti­tle means “un­cle” in Cantonese – are Hoi (Ben Yuen, above, left) and Pak (Tai Bo, above, right), who are well into their 60s and are lovers.</p>
    <p>Taxi driver Pak lives in fear of his wife and child dis­cov­er­ing his dou­ble life; Hoi, a di­vorced man who lives with less anx­i­ety, has to re­spect Pak’s bound­aries.</p>
    <p>The Cantonese-lan­guage film is be­ing screened as part of the Sin­ga­pore Chi­nese Film Fes­ti­val this year. It scored five nom­i­na­tions at last year’s Golden Horse Awards, in­clud­ing Lead Ac­tor for both Yuen and Tai.</p>
    <p>At this year’s Hong Kong Film Awards, Tai picked up the Best Ac­tor prize while Pa­tra Au, who plays Pak’s wife Ching, won Best Sup­port­ing Ac­tress. The film also earned a Best Pic­ture nomination at the awards.</p>
    <p>An­other work be­ing shown at the fes­ti­val is Bam­boo The­atre, a Hong Kong doc­u­men­tary about Chi­nese opera that was nom­i­nated for Best Doc­u­men­tary at last year’s Golden Horse Awards. Cin­ema and/or on­line screen­ings are avail­able.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Cin­ema screen­ings at Film­garde Cine­plexes Bugis+, Level 5 Bugis+, 201 Vic­to­ria Street; on­line screen­ings at Ki­noLounge by Shaw Or­gan­i­sa­tion (ki­nolounge.shaw.sg) WHEN: Till Sun­day</p>
    <p>AD­MIS­SION: $15 for cin­ema screen­ing, $12.99 for on­line screen­ing; talks and dis­cus­sions are free on­line</p>
    <p>INFO: scff.sg</p>

